{"continue": {"iistart": "2008-10-09T00:35:23Z", "continue": "||"}, "query": {"pages": {"29535": {"pageid": 29535, "ns": 6, "title": "File:NewtonsPrincipia.jpg", "imagerepository": "local", "imageinfo": [{"size": 258735, "width": 1266, "height": 842, "canonicaltitle": "File:NewtonsPrincipia.jpg", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/41/NewtonsPrincipia.jpg", "descriptionurl": "https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:NewtonsPrincipia.jpg", "descriptionshorturl": "https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?curid=29535", "extmetadata": {"DateTime": {"value": "2008-10-09 00:35:42", "source": "mediawiki-metadata", "hidden": ""}, "ObjectName": {"value": "NewtonsPrincipia", "source": "mediawiki-metadata"}, "CommonsMetadataExtension": {"value": 1.2, "source": "extension", "hidden": ""}, "Categories": {"value": "CC-Zero|Wren Library, Cambridge|Files with no machine-readable source|Pictures by Solipsist|Images without source|Title pages from the United Kingdom|Philosophiae Naturalis Principia Mathematica (1687 edition)|1687 title pages", "source": "commons-categories", "hidden": ""}, "Assessments": {"value": "", "source": "commons-categories", "hidden": ""}, "ImageDescription": {"value": "<p>Sir <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isaac_Newton\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Isaac Newton\">Isaac Newton</a>'s own first edition copy of his <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophiae_Naturalis_Principia_Mathematica\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Philosophiae Naturalis Principia Mathematica\">Philosophiae Naturalis Principia Mathematica</a> with his handwritten corrections for the second edition.\n</p><p>The first edition was published under the imprint of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samuel_Pepys\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Samuel Pepys\">Samuel Pepys</a> who was president of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Society\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Royal Society\">Royal Society</a>. By the time of the second edition, Newton himself had become president of the Royal Society,  as noted in his corrections.\n</p><p>It has been digitised by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cambridge_University_Library\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Cambridge University Library\">Cambridge University Library</a> and can be seen in the Cambridge Digital Library <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-ADV-B-00039-00001/\">[1]</a> along with other original works by Isaac Newton <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/collections/newton\">[2]</a>.\n</p>\nThe book can be seen in the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wren_Library,_Cambridge\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Wren Library, Cambridge\">Wren Library</a> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trinity_College,_Cambridge\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Trinity College, Cambridge\">Trinity College, Cambridge</a>.", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "Artist": {"value": "Isaac Newton", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "LicenseShortName": {"value": "CC0", "source": "commons-desc-page", "hidden": ""}, "UsageTerms": {"value": "Creative Commons Zero, Public Domain Dedication", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "AttributionRequired": {"value": "false", "source": "commons-desc-page", "hidden": ""}, "LicenseUrl": {"value": "http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/deed.en", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "Copyrighted": {"value": "True", "source": "commons-desc-page", "hidden": ""}, "Restrictions": {"value": "", "source": "commons-desc-page", "hidden": ""}, "License": {"value": "cc0", "source": "commons-templates", "hidden": ""}}, "mime": "image/jpeg"}]}}}}